Certainly! Here are five example sentences in Serbian that use the word "trka" in different forms and positions:

1. Danas ćemo gledati trku u Formuli 1. (*trku*, direct object) (Today we'll watch a race in Formula 1.)
2. On je pobedio na trci za trkače sa preponama. (*trci*, locative case) (He won the race for hurdle runners.)
3. Trka automobila održava se u nedelju. (*trka*, subject) (The car race takes place on Sunday.)
4. Mladi konj je spreman za trku. (*trku*, accusative case) (The young horse is ready for the race.)
5. Prijavio se za trku i već je počeo da trenira. (*trku*, direct object) (He signed up for the race and has already started training.)

I hope these examples help!